an operating system (os) is system software that manages computer hardware software resources and provides common services for computer programs time-sharing operating systems schedule tasks for efficient use of the system and may also include accounting software for cost allocation of processor time mass storage printing and other resources hardware functions such as input output memory allocation the operating acts as an intermediary between programs the computer hardware although application code is usually executed directly by frequently makes calls to an os function or is interrupted by it systems are found on many devices that contain a â€“ from cellular phones video game consoles to web servers supercomputers dominant general-purpose personal microsoft windows with a market share of around 7499% macos by apple inc in second place (1484%) varieties linux are collectively in third place (281%) in mobile sector (including smartphones tablets) android's share 7082% year 2020 according to third quarter 2016 data android's share on smartphones dominant with 875 percent with a growth rate 103 percent per year followed apple's ios 121 percent per year decrease market 52 while other systems amount just 03 percent[5] linux distributions are dominant server supercomputing sectors other specialized classes (special-purpose systems) such as embedded real-time exist many applications security-focused also exist some have low requirements (eg light-weight linux distribution) others may have higher requirements some require installation or may come pre-installed purchased computers (oem-installation) whereas others run directly from media (ie live cd) or flash memory (ie usb stick)